PromptCite Commercial License
=============================

PromptCite is dual-licensed:

  1. AGPL v3 (see LICENSE) for community use — individual students, developers,
     researchers, hobbyists, and non-commercial open-source projects.

  2. A separate commercial license is required for institutional and commercial
     deployment, as described in NOTICE.md.

A commercial license is REQUIRED for:

  - Universities, colleges, school districts, and academic-integrity offices
    that deploy PromptCite as part of any institutional service or
    recommended toolchain.
  - Edtech companies, LMS vendors, or any vendor bundling or integrating
    PromptCite into a paid product.
  - Any organization offering PromptCite as a managed or hosted service.

Commercial licenses preserve the AGPL v3 community license alongside —
purchasing a commercial license does not deprive the community of the AGPL
version, and AGPL contributions remain AGPL.

